Is there a significant difference in lobster size between MPA and non-MPA sites? In comparing these two sample populations,…

There is a .2% chance that we could have gotten sample means at least as different as ours if we sampled from populations with the same mean. Using a 95% confidence interval, we have sufficient evidence to reject the null hypothesis that the sample populations have the same mean. …..????
